# .trivyignore — suppressions for the Trivy fs and image scans.
#
# Format: one CVE ID per line. Include a comment block above each
# group with the *why*, the *what's-the-real-mitigation*, and a
# *revisit date* so future-us can re-evaluate.
#
# DO NOT add a CRITICAL CVE here without explicit security review.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# esbuild bundled Go stdlib CVEs — known false positives for our use
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# These are vulnerabilities in the Go stdlib (crypto/tls, net/url,
# archive/tar, archive/zip, crypto/x509) that get baked into the
# precompiled `esbuild` Go binaries shipped under
# `@esbuild/<platform>/bin/esbuild` in node_modules.
#
# Why these aren't reachable in BunMail:
#
#   * esbuild is a *build-time* tool — it reads `.ts`/`.js` files
#     from disk and writes `.js` files to disk. It does not parse
#     URLs from untrusted input, doesn't terminate TLS, doesn't
#     read tar/zip archives from the network.
#
#   * In our deployment, esbuild is pulled in transitively by
#     drizzle-kit. drizzle-kit only runs at container start time
#     during `bun run db:push`, against our own schema files, and
#     exits before the API listener accepts any traffic.
#
#   * Real fix tracked in #56 — move drizzle-kit out of the runtime
#     image into a build/migrate stage so esbuild never ships in
#     the published artifact. Once #56 lands these entries can be
#     removed and the scan stays green without suppression.
#
# Revisit: 2026-08-01 (or when #56 lands, whichever is sooner).
#
# From the newer esbuild@0.25.12 binary's bundled Go stdlib:
CVE-2025-68121
CVE-2025-58183
CVE-2025-61726
CVE-2025-61728
CVE-2025-61729
CVE-2026-25679
CVE-2026-32280
CVE-2026-32281
CVE-2026-32283
#
# From the older esbuild@0.18.20 nested under @esbuild-kit/core-utils
# (drizzle-kit dependency tree); same justification as above — esbuild
# is build-time only, the embedded Go stdlib vectors aren't reachable.
# Also goes away once #56 removes drizzle-kit from the runtime image.
CVE-2024-24790
CVE-2023-39325
CVE-2023-45283
CVE-2023-45288
